post_text: Hello Somers Families! Just a quick reminder that, in preparation for demolition of our old building, tomorrow will be the last chance for any drop-off if your student has any homework, books checked out from teachers, books checked out from the SMS Library, VMath books, Read 180 Books, Chromebooks or anything else that may have been borrowed by your student! All items must be turned in by 1:00 PM or else you may be charged the full costs of a replacement item (if applicable.) Please call 857-3661 if you have questions. Both the District and Somers Offices will be closed Thursday and Friday because of demolition prep - but will be available by email. The District Office will be available by phone or email by June 9th as they settle into their new space! (Woohoo!) Thank you so much.

Yearbook info -in case you missed this:
Here is a message from our SMS counselor about year books:

Hello LES and SMS Parents,

Here is a link to our yearbook order form for this year.
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfIy1QgOgpaH2Jus_Ja7Lu43d4oDCdI-DXiX2va1JcAvsYoDw/viewform

Please fill out one form for each student in your household, you can follow the link to fill out the form as many times as you need to. Yearbooks will be handed out at the beginning of next school year. Yearbooks are $10.00, and you can submit payment next year, before yearbooks are handed out. All 8th graders will all be receiving yearbooks this year, so please don't fill out an order form for your 8th grader, if you have another student in your household you would like to order a yearbook for, please fill out the form for that student.

If you have any questions please email me at erin.joronen@somersdist29.org.

Have a great day!

Erin

post_text:
Earlier today Governor Bullock announced that he will lift the state-wide school closure directive as of Thursday, May 7, but also noted that he is not suggesting that schools return to normal for the remainder of this school year.

We are currently working with other school districts in the Valley, and the Flathead City-County Health Department, in considering our safest options for the remainder of the school year.

While we recognize the hardships remote learning has created, the health and safety of our students, families, and staff remains our highest priority.

We will share more information with you in the coming days.

post_text:
Good morning Somers District Families. We know that there are a lot of questions and concerns at this time. One thing we know for certain, we will have PBJ, sack lunches available for pick-up throughout the week at no charge for our families. Please call this morning to the Somers Middle School office by 10:30 A.M. with the number of sack lunches you will need for today and the rest of the week. Pick up today will be at Somers Middle School from 11 AM to 1 PM. Starting tomorrow pick-ups will be at Lakeside AND Somers Schools from 11 AM to 1 PM.

Please know that our Administration is currently working on developing a plan that puts our families and communities' health & safety at the forefront. We will be communicating as often as possible, on all platforms, through this uncertain time. The District Office will be open on a modified schedule so please call and leave a message at 857-3661.

Thank you for your patience and for remaining “Somers Strong” through these next few weeks.
